1. Type "vim program.c"

2. Use the code on the screen for reference!

3. Instead of using arrow keys while making edits, try navigating with HJKL

4. Instead of copy pasting printf or re-writing it, use visual mode to select ONE line and paste it.

5. Come back to insert mode/replace mode to edit those statements.

6. Exit with ":wq"

7. Type "make program"

8. Type "./program" to see your hardwork pay off!

9. Wasn't this easy?
